==Old English==
===Etymology===
From [[ge-|ġe-]] + Germanic ''*mang-'', from Indo-European ''*menk-'' ‘knead’.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[gimang]].  The IE root is also the source of Slavic ''*mekъkъ'' (Old Church Slavonic [[мѫка]], Russian [[мука]]), Baltic ''*minki-'' (Lithuanian [[minkiti]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /je'maŋg/

===Noun===
'''ġemang''' ''n''
# a [[mixture]], a [[crowd]]

===Preposition===
'''ġemang'''
# [[among]]

